{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, SFT is now commonly combined with reinforcement learning (RL) to achieve finer control over model behavior [e. g 31].In RL, a model learns to make optimal decisions by interacting with an environment through trial and error, receiving feedback in the form of rewards or penalties to maximize its cumulative reward over time.",
    "Unlike SFT, in RL the model is not provided with explicit examples of the desired outputs.",
    "Instead, the GMPD must infer and explore autonomously, potentially uncovering novel solutions that might not have been anticipated.",
    "More technically, a pre-trained model is treated as a policy π θ (x) and updated to maximize a scalar reward -or equivalently, the probability over preferences-while constraining excessive deviation from its pre-trained distribution.",
    "Similarly to SFT, this process enables a transition from the unconditional distribution p(x) toward the desired conditional distribution p(x|y)."
  ]
}